Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in natural language processing (NLP) and presents mathematical analysis from information theory to show the efficacy of the proposed framework. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of stochasticity in the framework, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also presents initial experiments that depict the efficacy of the proposed framework, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of visual dialog, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper also discusses the applicability of the proposed framework to scalability, flexibility, and interpretability, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering).
